  "text": "The highest number of affected genes were found in the category proteolysis (23). Together with 11 genes differently regulated in protein metabolic process, this indicates that EE 2 exposure have large impact on the cellular and extracellular protein state in testis. GO-terms related to protein modification and protein metabolism has been shown to be the most affected biological processes in zebrafish males exposed to 5 ng/L EE 2 for 21 days during adulthood [CITATION_1] . In addition, the EE 2 exposure induced alterations in sperm quality in that study.",
